[color=#5b97bc]█▄ █ ▀█▀                           [head=3]Form 21B[/head] 
█ ▀█     █                     [head=3]Overtriage Authorization[/head]   [/color]

Holder is authorized to:  
☑ Diagnose one (1) paper cut as “critical condition”
☐ Declare “critical” status for stubbed toe  
☐ Request defib for minor bruising  
☑ Call for emergency blood transfusion for nosebleed
☑ Use the words “life-threatening” in casual conversation  

[color=#5b97bc][bold]Restrictions:[/bold][/color]  
• Not valid during mass casualty events
• Defibrillators may not be discharged more than once per bruising  
• Authorization void if patient is actually in critical condition  
• Overtriage limited to one (1) dramatization per shift  
• Not valid when reviewed by Chief Medical Officer

[color=#5b97bc][bold]Approved Usage Zone:[/bold][/color] Medical Ship  
[color=#5b97bc][bold]Expiration:[/bold][/color] Until first actual emergency   

[color=#aaaaaa][italic]Disclaimer: 
NanoTrasen is not responsible for wasted medical resources, panic caused in waiting areas, or NSFD detainment of staff who cry “wolf” too often. 
Form automatically expires if patient is pronounced dead.[/italic][/color]  
